01:28.443 --> 01:29.980
[Reporter] <i>Now that the
decades-in-the-making</i>

01:30.114 --> 01:31.984
<i>Tunnel and Reservoir Plan
is officially online,</i>

01:32.117 --> 01:34.523
<i>12 million gallons of storm
water will be diverted</i>

01:34.656 --> 01:37.227
<i>from municipal sewers
into the quarry.</i>

01:37.361 --> 01:38.664
<i>This should make homeowners</i>

01:38.797 --> 01:40.502
<i>accustomed to
flooding very happy.</i>

01:40.635 --> 01:43.206
Mary Romero, WZCH, Chicago.

01:43.340 --> 01:44.643
[keyboard clicks]

01:44.777 --> 01:45.645
So?

01:46.780 --> 01:48.450
We need more footage
of the tunnels.

01:48.584 --> 01:50.922
Tunnels are dark,
it might not read.

01:51.056 --> 01:54.295
Okay, then cut in more drone
footage above the reservoir.

01:54.428 --> 01:55.430
I just need the
viewers to understand

01:55.565 --> 01:56.901
the scope of this project.

01:57.034 --> 01:58.303
And limit your
own camera time.

01:58.436 --> 01:59.438
[Mary sighs]

01:59.573 --> 02:00.909
I don't understand you, Mary.

02:01.042 --> 02:02.579
Most people in this business

02:02.713 --> 02:04.549
would climb over their
colleagues to get on air.

02:04.683 --> 02:06.152
Well, I don't
like climbing, Phil.

02:06.285 --> 02:08.824
- I like reporting.
- [phone beeps]

02:08.958 --> 02:09.827
Yep.

02:09.960 --> 02:10.995
[Hank] <i>You busy?</i>

02:11.129 --> 02:12.197
Always.

02:12.331 --> 02:13.701
[Hank] <i>Get in here anyway.</i>

02:13.834 --> 02:14.936
[Mary chuckles]

02:15.070 --> 02:16.072
[phone beeps]

02:16.206 --> 02:17.141
All right, more drone footage.

02:17.275 --> 02:19.144
You got it, boss.

02:21.316 --> 02:24.589
[soft, bright music]

02:26.225 --> 02:27.027
- Think fast.
- [Mary gasps]

02:27.161 --> 02:28.163
[toy squeaks]

02:28.864 --> 02:30.668
This better not be
in lieu of my bonus.

02:30.802 --> 02:32.506
Come on, you remember
the Mistletoads.

02:32.639 --> 02:34.242
Back in the 80s,
they were all the rage.

02:34.375 --> 02:36.012
No, I think
I missed that party.

02:36.145 --> 02:37.515
Well, it's their
40th anniversary,

02:37.649 --> 02:39.351
and you're gonna do a
great story about them.

02:39.485 --> 02:40.722
[Mary giggles]

02:40.855 --> 02:42.091
That was a good one,
you almost got me.

02:42.224 --> 02:43.661
It's not a joke.

02:43.794 --> 02:44.696
What?

02:44.829 --> 02:46.099
It's not a joke.

02:46.232 --> 02:48.136
Why would we even consider
doing something like that?

02:48.270 --> 02:52.177
Because the Mistletoads
were made by Johnson Toys.

02:52.311 --> 02:54.015
Which is one of our
biggest advertisers.

02:54.148 --> 02:55.518
Our biggest advertiser.

02:55.651 --> 02:57.187
So, it's a
shameless puff piece.

02:57.320 --> 03:00.460
Oh no, a human interest
story about a trusted partner.

03:00.594 --> 03:01.597
Why do I have to do it?

03:01.731 --> 03:03.099
Because you're the best I got.

03:03.233 --> 03:04.401
Don't try and
butter me up, Hank.

03:04.536 --> 03:06.472
I'm not. This has
to be a solid piece.

03:06.607 --> 03:08.911
I need a primetime player
who can get me the goods.

03:09.044 --> 03:09.946
That's you.

03:10.079 --> 03:11.215
Okay, I just got a lead

03:11.348 --> 03:12.785
on the Transit Authority
expansion story.

03:12.919 --> 03:14.254
And we're gonna do that
story, just not right now.

03:14.388 --> 03:15.390
Then when?

03:15.525 --> 03:17.028
When the bills are paid.

03:17.161 --> 03:18.731
Look, times are changing.

03:18.864 --> 03:21.402
Some people say, we're
lucky to have jobs at all.

03:21.537 --> 03:22.939
Don't do this to me.

03:23.073 --> 03:24.510
Think of it this way.
If you get the story quick,

03:24.643 --> 03:25.945
you can be back
before Christmas.

03:26.078 --> 03:27.414
What do you mean, back?

03:27.549 --> 03:30.086
Johnson Toys is located
in Brunswick, Iowa.

03:30.220 --> 03:31.289
Thank you.

03:31.422 --> 03:32.792
Okay.

03:32.926 --> 03:35.230
If I do this, I want
complete creative control.

03:35.363 --> 03:36.867
- Done.
- No, I'm not joking.

03:37.001 --> 03:38.938
I want to tell the story the
way that I wanna tell it,

03:39.072 --> 03:40.340
with no input from the client.

03:40.473 --> 03:42.410
- You have my word.
- [Mary sighs]

03:42.545 --> 03:44.549
Look at the bright side,
no holiday traffic.

03:44.683 --> 03:45.484
Why not?

03:45.618 --> 03:46.921
Because last time I checked,

03:47.054 --> 03:48.824
Brunswick has a
population of about 1,000.

03:48.958 --> 03:50.528
[Mary scoffs]

03:51.495 --> 03:53.701
Now, it's 1,001.

03:53.835 --> 03:55.003
[toy squeaks]

03:55.470 --> 03:56.973
[Mary sighs]

03:58.443 --> 04:01.716
[soft, bright music]

04:05.691 --> 04:08.598
Okay, look, I don't know
what you are so upset about.

04:08.731 --> 04:10.033
Because I've spent
my entire career

04:10.166 --> 04:12.270
fighting for stories
that actually matter,

04:12.404 --> 04:13.774
to try and inspire change.

04:13.908 --> 04:15.444
And now, I'm shilling
for a toy company.

04:15.578 --> 04:16.747
It's not that bad.

04:16.881 --> 04:18.050
And soon enough,
you'll be telling them

04:18.183 --> 04:19.519
what stories to cover.

04:19.653 --> 04:21.188
[Mary chuckles]
You clearly don't know Hank.

04:21.322 --> 04:22.825
I know you're
living the dream.

04:22.959 --> 04:26.465
Expense accounts, flying
first class, limos.

04:26.600 --> 04:29.672
- Girl, I am driving myself.
- Ugh.

04:29.806 --> 04:31.309
Okay, the contractor
should be here

04:31.442 --> 04:32.712
first thing in the morning,

04:32.846 --> 04:33.914
and it should only
take a couple of days.

04:34.047 --> 04:36.018
Okay, it's no big deal.

04:36.152 --> 04:37.688
It is a big deal.

04:37.822 --> 04:39.325
I've been trying to get this
bathroom redone for months,

04:39.458 --> 04:40.594
and this is the only
week they could do it.

04:40.728 --> 04:42.632
Mary, it's all good.

04:42.766 --> 04:44.536
I have loads of
writing to catch up on.

04:44.669 --> 04:46.038
My publisher wants the
next three chapters

04:46.171 --> 04:47.441
by the end of the year,
so it's just nice

04:47.575 --> 04:48.744
to have somewhere to focus.

04:48.878 --> 04:49.478
Thank you.

04:49.612 --> 04:50.614
Okay, good.

04:50.748 --> 04:51.584
And Dylan's not gonna miss you?

04:51.717 --> 04:53.721
Dylan is fine, he's fine.

04:53.854 --> 04:56.159
Besides, it's like a
mini-vacation for me,

04:56.292 --> 04:57.428
before his family rolls in.

04:57.562 --> 04:59.633
Oh, right, oof.

05:00.167 --> 05:02.338
Mary, be real with me, though.

05:02.471 --> 05:04.809
Are you actually going
to Brunswick, Iowa?

05:04.943 --> 05:06.513
Of course, why would
I lie about that?

05:06.647 --> 05:07.648
Oh, I don't know.

05:07.782 --> 05:08.951
Maybe to get out
of a double date

05:09.084 --> 05:10.788
with us in Dylan's
business partner?

05:10.921 --> 05:12.926
Oh, Todd.

05:13.527 --> 05:15.463
Girl, don't even
pretend to be sorry.

05:16.399 --> 05:17.434
I gotta go.

05:17.568 --> 05:19.204
Saved by the bell.

05:19.338 --> 05:20.508
Have just the best time.

05:20.642 --> 05:22.444
Thank you, Brianna.

05:22.579 --> 05:25.584
This is Mary Romero,
reporting for Christmas.

05:25.718 --> 05:28.624
♪<i>♪ Let's make December ♪</i>

05:28.758 --> 05:33.033
♪<i>♪ A month to remember ♪</i>

05:33.166 --> 05:37.441
♪<i>♪ It's a magical feeling,
it's time for believing ♪</i>

05:37.576 --> 05:39.846
♪<i>♪ Better be ready, it's here ♪</i>

05:39.980 --> 05:43.453
♪<i>♪ Let's make December ♪</i>

05:43.588 --> 05:47.361
♪<i>♪ A month to remember ♪</i>

05:47.494 --> 05:50.300
[cars honk]

05:50.433 --> 05:52.070
[Mary] <i>You know what?</i>

05:52.204 --> 05:53.373
<i>I feel like the hits just
keep on coming there, Hank.</i>

05:53.508 --> 05:54.475
It's the best I can do, Mary.

05:54.610 --> 05:56.079
<i>I love working with Crash.</i>

05:56.212 --> 05:58.517
It's just, this isn't a
job for a one-man crew.

05:58.650 --> 06:00.053
And plus, he's
getting a little--

06:00.186 --> 06:01.790
Older?

06:01.924 --> 06:03.359
[Mary] <i>I was gonna say
crankier, if that's possible.</i>

06:03.492 --> 06:04.762
[Hank] <i>Look,
Crash's experience</i>

06:04.896 --> 06:06.199
<i>allows him to
pick up the slack.</i>

06:06.332 --> 06:07.836
Plus, you should be
grateful I'm sending him.

06:07.969 --> 06:09.773
A lot of stations are
requiring producers

06:09.906 --> 06:11.476
to shoot their own
footage nowadays.

06:11.610 --> 06:13.012
[Mary chuckles]

06:13.145 --> 06:15.217
Well, you're just a prince
among men there, Hank.

06:15.350 --> 06:16.285
Don't I know it.

06:16.418 --> 06:17.922
Drive safe.

06:18.724 --> 06:22.030
[mellow oldies music]

06:26.338 --> 06:30.647
